  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 889faa658c7b2c94ea4fff939bf8022e, type: 3}
  m_Name: DialogNPCArmourer
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Name: Patrizio
  Icon: {fileID: 7416670922274956215, guid: 67e11902f9a599344b5dc2f4b5a33db5, type: 3}
  HasInteraction: 0
  interactionType: 0
  Greeting: Patrick The Armourer
  Day1Dialog:
  - "You\u2019re new here, boy. The Ottomans have landed with hundreds of ships and
    tens of thousands of men. Their cannons roar from the hills, and every sword,
    pike, and cannon I maintain may save a life. \n<Press f to continue>"
  - We also have hoops of Greek fire ready for emergencies, and matchlock muskets
    line the walls. Even a small crack could spell death. Go to the anvil, survival
    here depends on preparation and courage.
  Day2FirstTimeDialog:
  - Cannonballs crash against our bastions. Each musket and sword I repair may save
    a Knight, and our hoops of Greek fire are ready if they reach the walls. Casualties
    are already mounting; even the best-prepared men fall if weapons fail.  Go to
    the anvil and start repairs!
  Day2MetBeforeDialog:
  - You return. Yesterday we tended muskets; today, check the new armour lined up
    for repairs. Each shot fired may hold the enemy at bay, and every weapon repaired
    prolongs life.  You know what to do, go to the anvil and start working.
  Day3FirstTimeDialog:
  - The walls tremble, boy. Ottoman engineers dig trenches, but our cannons roar
    back. Muskets misfire, swords splinter, pikes break. Dragut commands the artillery
    now, and men are falling daily. Even Greek fire may not save everyone.  Go to
    the anvil and start repairing what you can!  There is no time to loose!
  Day3MetBeforeDialog:
  - Yesterday, musket repairs; today, see the cannons ready with their carefully
    stacked cannonballs. Each shot could stop an assault. Lives hang on weapons and
    skill.  You know what to do boy!
  Day4FirstTimeDialog:
  - We are running low on iron, powder, and lead. Every musket and cannon I repair
    could stop an assault or fail, letting death through the gates. The enemy has
    brought engineers and reinforcements. The fort survives by grit and desperation.
  Day4MetBeforeDialog:
  - You return. Yesterday, muskets; today, cannonballs. We have fire hoops now that
    works great against the Ottoman's light cloths and is ready for breaches. Every
    shot may save a life, but the end draws nearer
  Day5FirstTimeDialog:
  - Tomorrow may be our last stand. Dragut oversees every shot, and we have only
    a fraction of the weapons we need. Every cannon, musket, and hoop of Greek fire
    I repair could be the difference between life and death.
  Day5MetBeforeDialog:
  - "This is it. You\u2019ve seen repairs, cannon care, muskets sharpened. Around
    half the defenders are dead. Every weapon might decide who survives when St.
    Elmo falls. Courage and preparation hang in the balance"
  dayNumber: 1
  metOnday1: 0
  metOnday2: 0
  metOnday3: 0
  metOnday4: 0
  metOnday5: 0
